    {
      "content": "High availability requirements for StorSimple",
      "pos": [
        4094,
        4139
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The hardware platform that is included with the StorSimple solution has enterprise-grade availability and reliability features that provide a foundation for a highly available, fault-tolerant storage infrastructure in your datacenter.",
      "pos": [
        4141,
        4375
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, there are requirements and best practices that you should comply with to help ensure the availability of your Azure StorSimple solution.",
      "pos": [
        4376,
        4521
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Before you deploy Azure StorSimple, carefully review the following requirements and best practices for the StorSimple device and connected host computers.",
      "pos": [
        4522,
        4676
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "High availability requirements and procedures for your StorSimple device",
      "pos": [
        4682,
        4754
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Review the following information carefully to ensure the high availability of your StorSimple device.",
      "pos": [
        4756,
        4857
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Power and Cooling Modules (PCMs)",
      "pos": [
        4864,
        4896
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "StorSimple devices include redundant, hot-swappable PCMs.",
      "pos": [
        4898,
        4955
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Each PCM has enough capacity to provide service for the entire chassis.",
      "pos": [
        4956,
        5027
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To ensure high availability, both PCMs must be installed.",
      "pos": [
        5028,
        5085
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Connect your PCMs to different power sources to provide availability if a power source fails.",
      "pos": [
        5090,
        5183
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If a PCM fails, request a replacement immediately.",
      "pos": [
        5187,
        5237
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Remove a failed PCM only when you have the replacement and are ready to install it.",
      "pos": [
        5241,
        5324
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Do not remove both PCMs concurrently.",
      "pos": [
        5328,
        5365
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The PCM module includes the battery.",
      "pos": [
        5366,
        5402
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Removing both of the PCMs will result in a no battery-protected shutdown.",
      "pos": [
        5403,
        5476
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Controller modules",
      "pos": [
        5483,
        5501
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "StorSimple devices include redundant, hot-swappable controller modules.",
      "pos": [
        5503,
        5574
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The controller modules operate in an active/passive manner.",
      "pos": [
        5575,
        5634
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "At any given time, one controller module is active and is providing service, while the other controller module is passive.",
      "pos": [
        5635,
        5757
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The passive controller module is powered on and becomes operational if the active controller module fails or is removed.",
      "pos": [
        5758,
        5878
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Each controller module has enough capacity to provide service for the entire chassis.",
      "pos": [
        5879,
        5964
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Both controller modules must be installed to ensure high availability.",
      "pos": [
        5965,
        6035
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Make sure that both controller modules are installed at all times.",
      "pos": [
        6039,
        6105
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If a controller module fails, request a replacement immediately.",
      "pos": [
        6109,
        6173
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Remove a failed controller module only when you have the replacement and are ready to install it.",
      "pos": [
        6177,
        6274
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Removing a module for extended periods will affect the airflow and hence the cooling of the system.",
      "pos": [
        6275,
        6374
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Make sure that the network connections to both controller modules are identical, and the connected network interfaces have an identical network configuration.",
      "pos": [
        6378,
        6536
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If a controller module fails or needs replacement, make sure that the other controller module is in an active state before replacing the failed controller module.",
      "pos": [
        6540,
        6702
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Do not remove both controller modules at the same time.",
      "pos": [
        6706,
        6761
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If a controller failover is in progress, do not shut down the standby controller module or remove it from the chassis.",
      "pos": [
        6765,
        6883
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "After a controller failover, wait at least five minutes before removing either controller module.",
      "pos": [
        6887,
        6984
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Network interfaces",
      "pos": [
        6992,
        7010
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "StorSimple device controller modules each have four 1 Gigabit and two 10 Gigabit Ethernet network interfaces.",
      "pos": [
        7012,
        7121
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Make sure that the network connections to both controller modules are identical, and the network interfaces that the controller module interfaces are connected to have an identical network configuration.",
      "pos": [
        7125,
        7328
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When possible, deploy network connections across different switches to ensure service availability in the event of a network device failure.",
      "pos": [
        7332,
        7472
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When unplugging the only or the last remaining iSCSI-enabled interface (with IPs assigned), disable the interface first and then unplug the cables.",
      "pos": [
        7476,
        7623
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the interface is unplugged first, then it will cause the active controller to fail over to the passive controller.",
      "pos": [
        7624,
        7741
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the passive controller also has its corresponding interfaces unplugged, then both the controllers will reboot multiple times before settling on one controller.",
      "pos": [
        7742,
        7904
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Connect at least two DATA interfaces to the network from each controller module.",
      "pos": [
        7908,
        7988
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you have enabled the two 10 GbE interfaces, deploy those across different switches.",
      "pos": [
        7992,
        8078
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When possible, use MPIO on servers to ensure that the servers can tolerate a link, network, or interface failure.",
      "pos": [
        8082,
        8195
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        8197,
        8523
      ],
      "content": "For more information about networking your device for high availability and performance, go to <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Install your StorSimple 8100 device<ept id=\"p1\">](storsimple-8100-hardware-installation.md#cable-your-storsimple-8100-device)</ept> or <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Install your StorSimple 8600 device<ept id=\"p2\">](storsimple-8600-hardware-installation.md#cable-your-storsimple-8600-device)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "SSDs and HDDs",
      "pos": [
        8530,
        8543
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "StorSimple devices include solid state disks (SSDs) and hard disk drives (HDDs) that are protected using mirrored spaces, and a hot-spare is provided for the HDDs.",
      "pos": [
        8545,
        8708
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Use of mirrored spaces ensures that the device is able to tolerate the failure of one or more SSDs or HDDs.",
      "pos": [
        8709,
        8816
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Make sure that all SSD and HDD modules are installed.",
      "pos": [
        8820,
        8873
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If an SSD or HDD fails, request a replacement immediately.",
      "pos": [
        8877,
        8935
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If an SSD or HDD fails or requires replacement, make sure that you remove only the SSD or HDD that requires replacement.",
      "pos": [
        8939,
        9059
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Do not remove more than one SSD or HDD from the system at any point in time.",
      "pos": [
        9063,
        9139
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "During replacement, monitor the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Hardware Status<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> in the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Maintenance<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> page for the drives in the SSDs and HDDs.",
      "pos": [
        9143,
        9259
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A green check status indicates that the disks are healthy or OK, whereas a red exclamation point indicates a failed SSD or HDD.",
      "pos": [
        9260,
        9387
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A failure of 2 or more disks of certain type (HDD, SSD) or consecutive failure within a short time frame may result in system malfunction and potential data loss.",
      "pos": [
        9391,
        9553
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If this occurs, contact technical support for assistance.",
      "pos": [
        9554,
        9611
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "We recommend that you configure cloud snapshots for all volumes that you need to protect in case of a system failure.",
      "pos": [
        9612,
        9729
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "EBOD enclosure",
      "pos": [
        9736,
        9750
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "StorSimple device model 8600 includes an Extended Bunch of Disks (EBOD) enclosure in addition to the primary enclosure.",
      "pos": [
        9752,
        9871
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An EBOD contains EBOD controllers and hard disk drives (HDDs) that are protected using mirrored spaces.",
      "pos": [
        9872,
        9975
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Use of mirrored spaces ensures that the device is able to tolerate the failure of one or more HDDs.",
      "pos": [
        9976,
        10075
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The EBOD enclosure is connected to the primary enclosure through redundant SAS cables.",
      "pos": [
        10076,
        10162
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Make sure that both EBOD enclosure controller modules, both SAS cables, and all the hard disk drives are installed at all times.",
      "pos": [
        10166,
        10294
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If an EBOD enclosure controller module or an HDD fails, request a replacement immediately.",
      "pos": [
        10298,
        10388
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If an EBOD enclosure controller module fails, make sure that the other controller module is active before you replace the failed module.",
      "pos": [
        10392,
        10528
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If an HDD fails or requires replacement, make sure that you remove only the HDD that requires replacement.",
      "pos": [
        10532,
        10638
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Do not remove an HDD until there is an indication that the disks and the array are healthy.",
      "pos": [
        10639,
        10730
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Do not remove more than one HDD from the system at any point in time.",
      "pos": [
        10734,
        10803
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        10807,
        11003
      ],
      "content": "During an EBOD controller module or HDD replacement, continuously monitor the status of the relevant component in the StorSimple Manager service by accessing <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Maintenance<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Hardware<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> status."
    },
    {
      "content": "If an SAS cable fails or requires replacement (Microsoft Support should be involved to make such a determination), make sure that you remove only the SAS cable that requires replacement.",
      "pos": [
        11007,
        11193
